{'name': "Rodney's Grill", 'address': '633 E Cabrillo Blvd', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Bars, Hotels, Restaurants, Steakhouses, Hotels & Travel, Seafood, Nightlife, Event Planning & Services, Wine Bars', 'hours': {'Tuesday': '17:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '17:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '17:0-22:0', 'Friday': '17:0-22:0', 'Saturday': '17:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': False, 'WiFi': 'paid', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': False, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2018-11-24 18:54:58', 'review_text': "Amazing dinner at Rodney's Grill.  The foie gras was the best I've ever eaten! And the steak with chantrells was heavenly!  Kudos to this new chef, Chef Moissin!!!  Thanks for making our Thanksgiving dinner so awesome!  Our waitress from Montenegro was super nice also!"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2018-11-23 02:15:24', 'review_text': "I know the chef is new and that the Hilton just took over this location, but we had our Thanksgiving dinner there today, and it felt like they had always been there. From the greeting at the door, to the service, the cocktails, the meals, it was excellent. Can't wait to go back for dinner on a non holiday. FYI the picky eater ate every single bit of his Turkey dinner... the lobster risotto was flawless with the fish course."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2017-11-11 03:48:11', 'review_text': 'I got the Pecan crusted halibut and it was amazingly scrumptious delicious awesomeness.   Whatever the buttery sauce was that comes with it literally made fireworks go off inside of me when I ate it.  

My wife had the Kansas City strip steak and it also was really good.  Her sauce was a red wine reduction and it was also incredible.  

We had the Parker station Pino Noir red wine and it was smooth and delicious.'}]}

{'name': 'Brasil Arts Cafe', 'address': '1230 State St, Ste C', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Juice Bars & Smoothies, Breakfast & Brunch, Brazilian, Restaurants, Food, Salad, Acai Bowls', 'hours': {'Monday': '17:0-20:30', 'Thursday': '17:0-20:30', 'Friday': '17:0-20:30', 'Saturday': '10:0-21:0', 'Sunday': '10:0-16:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-21 06:50:22', 'review_text': "Our hosts Roberta and Mestre Daniel Yoshimi (aka Prof. Chin) provided an excellent menu of the favorite foods of Brazil (o Brasil, em português). One who appreciates tasty-good food simply cannot stay away very long. My tri tip was delicious, and the multiple traditional sides were exactly on-point. (Prices are friendly too.)

I used to visit this establishment weekly to take part in great African drumming classes, and it's fun to revisit the festive atmosphere and food. They present their cuisine and culture with hospitality, nuance and great cooking skills.

#HighlyRecommended"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-18 05:28:16', 'review_text': 'my boyfriend and I went here for dinner and it was a nice experience :) we each got a caipirinha to drink which was good and my boyfriend LOVED the stroganoff! My Brazilian cesar was good and the brigadiero which we got to go was AMAZING! I would go back to try more! The lady told us to make ourselves at home which was a sweet sentiment!! The people were very nice :,)'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-15 12:06:28', 'review_text': 'The restaurant facility itself may not look all that elegant and appealing but the service and the food really blows that away. They serve food for each meal of the day but I personally would recommend going for breakfast and trying one of their acai fruit bowls. Slightly on the pricier side but so worth it and you will be healthily full for hours to come! The culture here is also something that is unique and interesting. Great place for family brunch!'}]}

{'name': 'JJ’s Diner', 'address': '413 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Diners, Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch', 'hours': {'Monday': '0:0-0:0', 'Tuesday': '7:30-13:30', 'Wednesday': '7:30-13:30', 'Thursday': '7:30-13:30', 'Friday': '7:30-13:30', 'Saturday': '7:30-14:0', 'Sunday': '8:0-14:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'valet': False, 'garage': False, 'street': False, 'lot': True, 'validated': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': None, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'divey': None, 'hipster': None, 'casual': None, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': None, 'intimate': None, 'romantic': None, 'classy': False, 'upscale': None}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-30 20:27:18', 'review_text': 'My husband and I were looking for a breakfast place while staying in Santa Barbara. We walked by this place and decided to try it out. First we were greeted with kind smiles and did not have to wait to be seated. Michael was our server and he was so so so kind! We ordered the Chile Verde Omelette and Eggs with Bacon. We received our food fast! The food was great, the service was amazing, and the environment was great!

Give this place a try!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-29 01:04:47', 'review_text': 'Great breakfast and service. Highly recommend. Staff even took care of noisy transients as they came on by - thank goodness !'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-28 19:02:22', 'review_text': "The wait to be seated was short despite the long line, they work quickly to get your food in front of you. The Customer service at this place is awesome and deserves 5 stars by itself. They are very friendly, prompt, and kept our coffees filled. If you notice the other reviews where Karens were complaining about bad service, were leaving reviews around when covid peaked so don't pay attention to those. I assure you the service is great.

The food is not bad, however it is basic, and safe. Don't get me wrong,  the food tasted fine, it's just that they play it safe which I guess is a good thing so that Karens in SB (There are plenty in this town) don't complain."}]}

{'name': 'Subway', 'address': '3967 State St Space 4, Space 4', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Sandwiches, Breakfast & Brunch, Restaurants, Fast Food', 'hours': {'Monday': '8:0-22:0', 'Tuesday': '8:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '8:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '8:0-22:0', 'Friday': '8:0-22:0', 'Saturday': '8:0-22:0', 'Sunday': '9:0-21:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2020-11-02 05:34:38', 'review_text': "My kid loves Subway. I appreciate their wide selection, their consistency, and their price point, which is dirt cheap for SB. Chances are you like it too, or it wouldn't be the largest fast-food franchise in the country by number of stores. I wish there were 3.5 stars, because that seems more fair. 

This shop is tiny and tucked away in the 5 points center. They have a few tables out front, but it's not a great place to eat unless you're really hungry. They are generally very friendly, although one time I forgot to ask for my free cookie up front and they refused to give it to me. Their cookies aren't any good anyways so they can keep it, but it seemed like a silly decision. Maybe I'll get my kid to TP the place when she's a teenager. 

Anyway, Valentinos, South Coast, Sam's, Plaza Deli, and Fresco all have better sandwiches but not as cheap and maybe your kids love Subway too. Certainly a reasonable option."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-04-21 23:17:40', 'review_text': "Sandwiches were really good wasn't expecting much but honestly as blown away keep up the good work"}, {'review_stars': 1.0, 'review_date': '2016-03-31 19:45:20', 'review_text': "The employees didn't seem to care, they also didn't cut the bread correctly and the sandwich was falling apart. Make the trip to another subway, it'll be worth it."}]}

{'name': 'Dogtown', 'address': '888 Embarcadero Del N', 'city': 'Isla Vista', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Hot Dogs, Restaurants', 'hours': {'Monday': '11:0-22:0', 'Tuesday': '11:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '11:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '11:0-3:0', 'Friday': '11:0-3:0', 'Saturday': '11:0-3:0', 'Sunday': '11:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': None, 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2012-06-28 16:27:59', 'review_text': 'Had a BBQ Burger and Crisscut fries from this location which was very delicious. However, this restaurant is no longer here and is being replaced with The Habit Burger [!!!!].'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2012-06-14 00:40:03', 'review_text': 'This is my favorite place in Isla Vista hands down.  Not only are the hotdogs/sausages great but their burgers are surprisingly the cheapest and most delicious in town!  It does not end there, the sweet potatoe fries are AMAZINGLY delicious, affordable and plentiful!'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2012-04-11 03:18:49', 'review_text': "This place was a go-to when I lived in Isla Vista.  I'd always go for hotdog, sourkraut and mustard, simple and delicious. 

What really sets this place a part from your average hot-dog joint are the dogtown fries.  Think of them as Nacho fries.  They are so amazing.  The fries are loaded with beans, guacamole, onions, jalapenos, grated cheese, & bacon bits.  

These alone give them 4/5 stars. The missing star is the price (but really, what isn't over priced in Isla Vista) and for being a hot dog place, I really wish the hot dogs were amazing instead of okay."}]}

{'name': 'Reds Bin 211', 'address': '211 Helena Ave', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food, Bars, Tapas Bars, Restaurants, Pubs, Wine Bars, Nightlife, Coffee & Tea', 'hours': {'Tuesday': '15:0-1:0', 'Wednesday': '15:0-1:0', 'Thursday': '15:0-1:0', 'Friday': '15:0-1:0', 'Saturday': '13:0-1:0', 'Sunday': '13:0-1:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': False, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': True, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2016-04-30 05:17:13', 'review_text': 'Reds Bin is a chill lil spot in Santa Barbara I have come to frequent. If you get sick of the State Street scene and want a bit of a different, more relaxed vibe, I would go to Reds. The bar food is also super yummy, and the bartenders are lovely people. I really love this place.'}, {'review_stars': 1.0, 'review_date': '2016-04-23 01:42:23', 'review_text': 'Not a fan of a place who likes to serve alcohol to underage kids...... Prob should think bout hiring some new bartenders.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2016-03-29 22:03:46', 'review_text': 'This place was so fun. Great cocktails. Great vibe. 

My boyfriend and I hung out here while we were visiting Santa Barbara on a saturday night. There was ample seating (which is a huge deal to me). 

The bartenders were super great and it seemed like a place for locals. Not touristy which was great.'}]}

{'name': 'Revolver', 'address': '1429 San Andres St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Pizza', 'hours': {'Wednesday': '16:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '16:0-22:0', 'Friday': '16:0-22:0', 'Saturday': '16:0-22:0', 'Sunday': '16:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': None, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': None, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'divey': True, 'hipster': None, 'casual': None, 'touristy': None, 'trendy': True, 'intimate': None, 'romantic': None, 'classy': None, 'upscale': False}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-06 20:15:13', 'review_text': "Nothing derails my good intentions of starting a diet like a Revolver Pizza craving! It's absolutely the BEST!! Beautifully handmade crust and fresh toppings. Not fancy just delicious. And the salads are incredible. Best Caesar with real anchovy dressing. Market salad has yummy dill ranch, shaved vegetables on yummy lettuce. I don't love the atmosphere, so we always get it to go. It's super popular so get your order in early! But it's definitely our favorite pizza in SB."}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-01 06:13:46', 'review_text': 'Great pizza but limited toppings odd hours and long wait time for food.

They really should open at 11am like any other normal pizza place.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-20 02:58:37', 'review_text': "Hands down the best dang pizza in all of Santa Barbara. Not even close. Simple menu and from the crisp on the crust and bottom to the tang in the red sauce, SB you have a winner. It's artisan pizza meets NY on the west coast. Proves you don't need to be in the funk zone to have something great and feels like Brooklyn back 20
Years ago in the fact that they are hip but hard working and making something great. The Caesar salad had a great dressing and fresh greens to boot."}]}

{'name': 'Coast Restaurant & Bar', 'address': 'Canary Hotel, 31 W Carrillo St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Event Planning & Services, American (New), Party & Event Planning, American (Traditional)', 'hours': {'Monday': '7:0-22:0', 'Tuesday': '7:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '7:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '7:0-22:0', 'Friday': '7:0-23:0', 'Saturday': '7:0-23:0', 'Sunday': '7:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': True, 'lot': True, 'valet': True}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': False, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': True, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2015-06-28 02:55:51', 'review_text': 'My wife and I went for a special evening out.  The lounge setting and ambience was wonderful and relaxing. The dinning room had subtle elegance.  The bread was warm and tasty, butternut squash soup and the romaine wedge salad was delicious. The service was outstanding. All was wonderful until the main course. The short  ribs tasted like pot roast and the New York steak was ok-needed salt.  We really wanted it to be great but the main dishes lacked flavor. Now for dessert... Butterscotch pudding and lemon cheesecake were excellent.  We really wanted to give 4 stars but 3 is all we can give it.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2013-03-20 03:27:00', 'review_text': "We were all very tired after a long day of work and being on the road, so we decided to try the restaurant in our hotel, which was conveniently located in our hotel's lobby.

We started our evening sharing the roasted California mussels seasoned perfectly and served with sourdough bread.  Then for our main course my daughter and I shared the savory manilla clams served over hand cut tagliatelle seasoned with basil, lemon and chile.  My husband ordered the crisy duck breast over potato gnocci and told both the waiter and I how he was in heaven that they had created a dish with two of his favorite meals put together in one.  We topped off the night with a bottle of Conundrum wine and a serving of their warm, comforting bread pudding and ice cream and called it a night!

The service was friendly and quick, and the food was delicious.  We will definitely be back the next time we're visiting the wonderful city of Santa Barbara!"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2013-03-16 18:15:54', 'review_text': 'We decided to eat at Coast tonight because we wanted to try something different in Santa Barbara.  We ordered  the mussels, the pork belly sliders, shishito peppers and the pork ribs everything we had was really very good but the real stand out were the mussels the sauce was accompanied with a sourdough toast that was delicious.  Just before we left James Siao the head chef came out and talked to us we told him how he really enjoyed the meal.'}]}
